CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 27, 1945, pg. 13, reads: "Another Champ - Here's Billie Spellman and his prize show horse, who gave the fans a thrilling exhibition. Tow more horses from Joe Louis stable- Allen's Walking Jim and Allen's Pride - won first and second prize in walking horse grand championship.- Photo by Harris."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Billie Spellman wearing hat and tweed suit jacket, standing behind spotted horse with saddle and bridle, lying on straw in Hunt Armory during horse show
